-1  What ***git*** command creates a branch?
  git branch

-2  What is the difference between a fast-forward and recursive merge?
  Fast-forward: Git moves the pointer to the last commit of the merged branch when there are no divergent changes.  
  Recursive: Git creates a new merge commit when there are diverging commits between branches.

-3  What ***git*** command changes to another branch?
  git switch

-4  What ***git*** command deletes a branch?
  git branch -d

-5  How do merge conflicts happen?
  Merge conflicts occur when Git cannot automatically reconcile changes between two branches, such as modifying the same line in a file or conflicting changes to file structures
